excerpt: San Carlos de Bariloche (commonly called Bariloche) is a town in Argentina’s Patagonia region. It borders Nahuel Huapi, a large glacial lake surrounded by the Andes Mountains. Bariloche is known for its Swiss alpine-style architecture and its chocolate, sold in shops lining Calle Mitre, the main street. It's also a popular base for hiking and skiing the nearby mountains and exploring the surrounding Lake District.
detail_description: San Carlos de Bariloche, also known as Bariloche, is a charming town located in Argentina's Patagonia region. It sits on the shores of Nahuel Huapi, a stunning glacial lake surrounded by the majestic Andes Mountains. The town is famous for its Swiss alpine-style architecture and delicious chocolate sold in numerous shops along Calle Mitre, the main street.
name: San Carlos de Bariloche
address: Río Negro Province, Argentina

excerpt: Recreational mountain featuring a sizable winter ski center & summertime trails with lake views.
detail_description: Cerro Catedral is a popular recreational mountain in Argentina, known for its sizable winter ski center and summertime trails offering stunning lake views. The area around Refugio Frey has seen significant improvements since 2005, with over 90 routes being re-equipped for safer climbing experiences. As the largest ski center in Argentina and South America, Cerro Catedral boasts 53 tracks catering to skiers, snowboarders, and alpine skiers of all levels.
name: Cerro Catedral
address: Río Negro Province, Argentina

detail_description: Cerro Campanario, often hailed as one of the top 5 best views globally, offers breathtaking panoramic vistas that seem to extend endlessly in every direction. The short but challenging 30-40 minute hike leads to a viewing platform providing different orientations over all the lakes. At the summit, visitors can also enjoy souvenir shopping and take in the stunning scenery through a 180-degree window at the cafe.
name: Cerro Campanario
address: Confitería Cerro Campanario, Av. Exequiel Bustillo 17500, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

excerpt: Simple guesthouse in a national park offering no-frills dorms, a guest kitchen & dining.
detail_description: Refugio Frey is a simple guesthouse located in a national park, offering basic dorms, a guest kitchen, and dining facilities. Unlike other mountain refuges in Bariloche that are open seasonally, Refugio Frey welcomes visitors year-round and caters to backcountry skiers and mountaineers during the winter months.
name: Refugio Frey
address: Río Negro, Argentina

excerpt: Landmark town hall & main square of Bariloche, featuring Alpine-inspired architecture & a museum.
detail_description: Centro Cívico Bariloche is the focal point of the town, featuring Alpine-inspired architecture and a museum that showcases the region's history. The buildings, constructed from timber and local stone, were designed in 1939 by Ernesto de Estrada in collaboration with renowned architect Alejandro Bustillo. At the main plaza, an equestrian statue of General Roca stands amidst graffiti art.
name: Centro Cívico Bariloche
address: Centro Cívico, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

excerpt: Colonia Suiza is a village in Río Negro Province in Patagonia, Argentina. Dotted with chalets that recall its Swiss pioneer past, it lies beside Lago Perito Moreno in the Lake District, amid a landscape of snow-capped Andean mountains, glacial lakes and forests. The village market is known for curanto, a stew cooked on hot rocks in the ground. To the north, Parque Nacional Nahuel Huapi offers trails and waterfalls.
detail_description: Colonia Suiza is a charming village located in Río Negro Province, Patagonia, Argentina. The area is rich in Swiss heritage and features picturesque chalets nestled amidst the stunning landscape of snow-capped Andean mountains, glacial lakes, and lush forests. Visitors can explore the local market known for its traditional dish called curanto, a stew cooked on hot rocks in the ground.
name: Colonia Suiza
address: Río Negro Province, Argentina

excerpt: Accessible via a cable car, this mountain offers hiking, biking & seasonal cross-country ski trails.
detail_description: Cerro Otto, located within Nahuel Huapi National Park, is a mountain that offers breathtaking panoramic views of Lago Nahuel Huapi and the Andes from its 1,405-meter summit. Accessible by car, foot, or cable car, it provides hiking and biking trails in addition to seasonal cross-country ski trails. While the cable cars may undergo maintenance at times, visitors can still enjoy the stunning scenery and outdoor activities such as skiing during winter.
name: Cerro Otto
address: San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro Province, Argentina

excerpt: Museum with guided tours & exhibits exploring the history of chocolate, plus a gift shop & cafe.
detail_description: If you're a chocolate lover, the Museo del Chocolate Havanna is an absolute must-visit! Nestled next to Cerro Viejo, this charming museum offers guided tours that delve into the fascinating history of chocolate. You'll get a glimpse of how chocolate is crafted and even see impressive sculptures made entirely from this beloved treat. The experience includes tasting their delicious hot chocolate, which adds a delightful touch to your visit.
name: Museo del Chocolate Havanna
address: Av. Exequiel Bustillo 1200, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

excerpt: The beach at Playa Bonita is lapped by the cold, wind-rippled waters of Lake Nahuel Huapi, popular with kayakers, scuba divers, and windsurfers. Anglers go fly fishing for brook trout off nearby Huemul Island. Alpine-style cafes and steakhouses line the shore, with Patagonian ales made and sold at Kunstmann, a landmark brewpub. Traditional bakeries and grocery stores offer supplies for a beach picnic.
detail_description: Playa Bonita is a picturesque beach on the shores of Lake Nahuel Huapi, attracting water sports enthusiasts such as kayakers, scuba divers, and windsurfers. Nearby Huemul Island offers excellent fly fishing opportunities for brook trout. The area is dotted with alpine-style cafes, steakhouses, traditional bakeries, and grocery stores providing supplies for beach picnics.
name: Playa Bonita
address: San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro Province, Argentina

excerpt: Cathedral with a park-like lakefront setting featuring stained glass depictions of Biblical stories.
detail_description: The Cathedral Our Lady of Nahuel Huapi, also known as Nuestra Senora de Nahuel Huapi, is a monumental neo-gothic building located in Bariloche next to the lake. Designed by architect Alejandro Bustillo and completed in 1947, this cathedral boasts impressive walls, a gigantic dome, and stunning stained-glass windows depicting biblical stories and historical figures from the area.
name: Cathedral Our Lady of Nahuel Huapi
address: Vice Almte. O'Connor 500, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

excerpt: This expansive alpine lake offers swimming, kayaking, fishing, hiking trails & mountain biking.
detail_description: Gutiérrez Lake, located in the Nahuel Huapi National Park in Argentina, offers a range of outdoor activities such as swimming, kayaking, fishing, hiking trails and mountain biking. The northern end of the lake features Villa Los Cohiues with a campground and a beautiful beach ideal for swimming due to its warm waters. Visitors can enjoy stunning views of the surrounding mountains from this area. The lake is easily accessible via Route 40, known for its scenic beauty.
name: Gutiérrez Lake
address: Río Negro Province, Argentina

excerpt: Chocolate store & ice cream parlor in elegant surrounds, with an indoor ice-skating rink.
detail_description: Rapanui is a popular chocolate store and ice cream parlor in Bariloche, with an elegant art-deco inspired design. The sprawling premises offer a variety of chocolate products, from animals to gift packages, and also feature a cafe serving tasty treats and quick bites. One of the highlights is the indoor ice-skating rink. Rapanui's high-quality products have made it a favorite among locals and tourists alike.
name: Rapanui
address: Mitre 202, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: Alto El Fuego is a charming restaurant nestled in San Carlos de Bariloche, housed in a beautifully restored wooden building dating back to 1941. This inviting eatery sits on a hill near the Civic Center and boasts an open grill that greets you as soon as you step inside. The ambiance is minimalist yet warm, making it the perfect spot for both locals and visitors alike, including many international guests.
name: Alto El Fuego
address: 20 de Febrero 451, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: Mitre Street is a charming cobblestone thoroughfare, renowned for its array of quaint shops, delightful chocolate boutiques, cozy hotels, and inviting restaurants. The street boasts spacious walkways that provide a pleasant pedestrian experience without the hassle of navigating through bustling crowds or vehicular traffic.
name: Mitre
address: R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: Berlina is a popular spot for apres-ski activities, drawing in skiers and snowboarders with its casual atmosphere and homemade pizzas. The microbrewery offers an enticing selection of craft beers, making it the perfect place to unwind after a day on the slopes. While service may be a bit slow, visitors rave about the delicious pizza and solid beer options.
name: Berlina
address: Calle al cerro Complejo La Base, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: Cascada de Los Duendes is a picturesque trail in the Gutierrez Lake Sector of Nahuel Huapi National Park. The route combines two short trails, leading to the beautiful double waterfall hidden in the forest. After enjoying the cascading waters, hikers can continue along a slightly sloping path to reach Mirador del Lago Gutierrez, offering stunning panoramic views of the area. This easily accessible walk is suitable for families and can be enjoyed year-round with minimal difficulty.
name: Cascada de los Duendes
address: San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: Seven Lakes Travel is a popular choice for travelers visiting Bariloche, offering car rental services and custom packages for both summer and winter seasons. The company provides well-maintained vehicles at competitive rates, making it an affordable option for exploring the area. Customers have praised the helpful staff who assist in arranging outings and providing valuable information about the most beautiful places to visit in Bariloche.
name: Seven Lakes Travel & Rent A Car
address: Entre Pinos 1 59, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

excerpt: Museum of paleontology with displays of regional fossils, including dinosaur skeletons.
detail_description: The Bariloche Paleontological Museum is a fascinating destination for those interested in the region's natural history. The museum showcases a variety of regional fossils, including dinosaur skeletons that are hundreds of millions of years old. Visitors can explore exhibits featuring ancient artifacts and even a dinosaur egg. Although the museum is small, it offers well-organized displays and friendly hosts who provide insightful explanations about the exhibits. While some visitors note that the museum could be better maintained, many appreciate its intriguing collection and informative presentations.
name: Bariloche Paleontological Museum
address: Av, Av. 12 de Octubre, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: Tronador is a popular hiking destination in Patagonia, with a typical route spanning 8.7 miles and offering moderate to challenging difficulty. Starting from Bariloche, hikers can access the trail via buses connecting from nearby towns. Known as the gateway to Patagonia, Bariloche boasts picturesque lakes, mountain peaks, and ski lifts during winter.
name: Tronador
address: R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

excerpt: Chairlift ride up 1,050m-high Cerro Campanario, with lake & mountain vistas & a cafe at the top.
detail_description: Confitería del Cerro Campanario is a must-see destination in Bariloche, offering breathtaking panoramic views from its summit. Visitors can reach the top by foot, car, or a scenic chairlift ride that ascends 1,050 meters above sea level. Once at the peak, multiple platforms provide 360-degree views of the surrounding mountains and Patagonian lakes. This iconic location is part of Circuito Chico and offers an unforgettable experience for travelers seeking stunning natural beauty.
name: Confitería Cerro Campanario
address: Av. Exequiel Bustillo 17500, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

name: CAU CAU - Isla Victoria y Bosque de Arrayanes
address: Mitre 139, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: Frantom is a renowned chocolate factory in Bariloche, founded by the Fenoglio family. The founders are passionate about creating high-quality chocolate using excellent raw materials. The owners, Don Diego and his sons Franco and Tomas, are dedicated to perfecting their craft. Visitors can observe the chocolate-making process through glass windows and sample some of the products. Frantom offers a wide variety of chocolates filled with local jams, jellies, fruits, and alcohol.
name: Frantom
address: Mitre 201, Quaglia 111, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: Mirador Lago Gutierrez is a family-friendly hike that takes you through stunning forests, past rivers and waterfalls, and up to a rocky bluff with panoramic views of Lake Gutierrez and the surrounding mountains. The easy walking path takes about 20-30 minutes at a regular pace, making it accessible for most visitors. It's recommended to bring along a small picnic or beverage to enjoy while taking in the scenery.
name: Mirador Lago Gutierrez
address: San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: This outdoor sports store is a beautiful place with amazing views, and it has a great selection of gear for both hiking and skiing. It's a little more expensive than other stores, but the quality of the products is definitely worth it. The staff are extremely helpful, and they will go out of their way to help you find what you're looking for.
name: Patagonia Showroom
address: Palacios 151, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: Fábrica Cerveza Blest proudly holds the title of being the first craft brewery in the city, starting as a small factory 30 years ago and now expanding to 4 locations in Bariloche and additional franchises across the country. This relaxed restaurant and brewery is suitable for both family outings and lively adult nights. While microbrews are gaining popularity in Argentina, Blest has been a pioneer in beer production for three decades.
name: Fábrica Cerveza Blest
address: Alaniz J. 230, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: One of the most famous local chocolatier chains has expanded to Rapa Nui's airport, offering a smaller selection compared to its city center stores. Despite the limited options, it provides travelers with a convenient opportunity to indulge in locally made chocolates before or after their flights.
name: Rapa Nui
address: Acceso A Aeropuerto Internacional Tte. L. Candelar 8400, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

excerpt: Activity park featuring ziplines, sledding, snow tubing, skiing, hiking & other winter activities.
detail_description: Piedras Blancas is a winter wonderland offering a variety of activities for all ages. From ziplines and snow tubing to skiing and hiking, there's something for everyone. For the more adventurous, sports climbing below Cerro Otto provides stunning views of Nahuel Huapi and the surrounding mountains. While the park offers fun at lower prices than nearby ski resorts, visitors should be prepared for potentially expensive food and beverage costs on-site.
name: Piedras Blancas
address: Acceso Cerro Otto, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

excerpt: Museum tracing the natural & cultural history of Patagonia with a range of dioramas & artifacts.
detail_description: The Francisco Moreno Museum of Patagonia is a must-visit attraction in the plaza, offering an intriguing exploration of the natural and cultural history of Patagonia. The museum showcases a diverse range of exhibits, including dioramas, artifacts, and even a caricature featuring Perito Moreno and Theodore Roosevelt. Visitors can admire engraved Tehuelche tablet stones, Aonikenk painted horse-hides, and unique items like playing cards made from guanaco skin.
name: Francisco Moreno Museum of Patagonia
address: Centro Cívico S/n, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: Nestled around kilometer 12 on Avenida Bustillo, Bahía Serena is a serene inlet that offers one of the most breathtaking views of Lake Nahuel Huapi without the need for a strenuous hike. This charming spot features a sandy beach perfect for lounging with a blanket while soaking in stunning sunsets over the mountains. The area is ideal for relaxation and adventure alike, with opportunities to rent kayaks and explore the crystal-clear waters fed by pure snowmelt.
name: Bahía Serena
address: Av. Exequiel Bustillo 12133-12299, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: Cerro López, located in Bariloche, can be reached via a route starting from 'la pancheria' on the Circuito Chico. The trail follows Arroyo Lopez and offers stunning views of Cerro Lopez, Cerro Llao Llao, and Lago Nahuel Huapi.
name: Cerro López
address: R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: Punto Panorámico - Circuito Chico offers an exclusive lookout point that takes full advantage of its location to provide visitors with a prestigious spot to enjoy the unique landscapes of Bariloche. The wooden deck with comfortable chairs overlooks a network of lakes, green-clad mountains, and hills, making it a must-visit for first-time visitors.
name: Punto Panorámico - Circuito Chico
address: Cto. Chico, San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: Rafting Far South offers an amazing experience in the Rio Manso. The team is friendly, knowledgeable, and fun. The package includes transport from the hotel and a simple breakfast with options to purchase lunch (Patagonian Asado) and photos or videos of the run. Extremo Sur provides a full-day rafting adventure deep into the National Park, offering an excellent rafting experience with picturesque views.
name: Rafting Far South

detail_description: Experience the thrill of nature with the Rafting Adventure Bariloche, a perfect way to immerse yourself in the stunning landscapes of Argentine Patagonia. This adventure package offers an exhilarating level 3/4 rafting journey that takes you down to the Chilean border. Led by highly skilled guides, including the charismatic Chimango, you'll transform from tourists into a cohesive rafting team while navigating exciting rapids.
name: Rafting Adventure Bariloche
address: Mitre 131, R8400 Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: When visiting San Carlos de Bariloche, one of the must-see attractions is Circuito Chico. Whether you choose to explore it on foot or by car, this scenic route offers breathtaking views of Lake Moreno and the surrounding landscapes. Make sure to make a stop at Llao Llao for a leisurely walk and take in the beauty of the area. Visitors have described it as a beautiful and easy tour, with stunning viewpoints that offer picturesque photo opportunities.
name: Circuito Chico San Carlos De Bariloche
address: RP77, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: Ice Bariloche is a unique gem located in the heart of the city, renowned for being the largest ice bar in South America. This extraordinary venue features stunning ice sculptures and maintains a chilly atmosphere at -3 degrees Celsius. However, there's no need to worry about the cold; upon entry, guests are provided with thermal layers and gloves to ensure comfort. Inside Ice Bariloche, patrons can enjoy drinks served in glasses made entirely of ice, adding an extra touch of novelty to their experience.
name: Ice Bariloche
address: España 476, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

name: Los Curantos de Víctor Goye
address: Colonia, Suiza, San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: Almazén de Sabores is a cozy establishment located near the owners' residence, offering the most satisfying gastronomic experience discovered during a ten-day stay in Argentina. With affordable prices for US visitors taking advantage of the strong dollar exchange rate, this hidden gem provides an appetizer sampler featuring five delectable items that are beautifully presented. Their stuffed chicken and lamb kabob dishes were particularly outstanding, complemented by delightful whole-wheat bread.
name: Almazén de Sabores
address: Los Radales 667, R8402 Dina Huapi, Río Negro, Argentina

excerpt: Cozy suites & apartments, some with saunas, in a hilltop retreat, plus lake-view dining & a pool.
detail_description: Nestled in the picturesque hills of San Carlos de Bariloche, Charming Luxury Lodge & Private Spa is a serene retreat that promises an unforgettable experience. This luxurious haven features cozy suites and exclusive bungalows, many equipped with private hot tubs and saunas for ultimate relaxation. Guests can indulge in breathtaking views of Nahuel Huapi Lake while enjoying delectable dining options or unwinding by the pool.
name: Charming Luxury Lodge & Private Spa
address: Hua Huan 7549, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

excerpt: Warm bungalows with kitchens in a charming golf resort offering pools, sport courts & a spa.
detail_description: Nestled within the serene Arelauquen Golf and Polo Club, Arelauquen Bungalows Hoyo 3 offers a delightful retreat for those seeking both relaxation and recreation. These warm bungalows come equipped with kitchens, making them perfect for self-catering stays. Guests can enjoy a variety of amenities including indoor and outdoor swimming pools, tennis courts, and even squash facilities. The property boasts 24-hour security, ensuring peace of mind during your stay.
name: Arelauquen Bungalows Hoyo 3
address: Arelauquen Golf and Polo Country Club, R8401 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: If you're looking for a unique way to explore the stunning landscapes of Bariloche, consider Cabalgatas La Fragua - Estancia San Ramón. This horseback riding experience offers an unforgettable adventure, perfect for families and riders of all skill levels. Guests are welcomed with a delightful breakfast before embarking on a scenic two-hour ride through breathtaking scenery. The gentle horses make it accessible even for children and those new to riding.
name: The Forge Horseback Riding (San Ramon Ranch)
address: Villegas 222, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

name: Playa del Moreno Sin Viento
address: San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro Province, Argentina

name: Residente Café Bistró
address: Libertad 275, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

excerpt: Simple dorms & private rooms in a relaxed hostel offering a bar & a communal kitchen.
detail_description: Hopa Home Patagonia Hostel & Bar is a relaxed accommodation option in San Carlos de Bariloche, conveniently situated near the beach and city center. The hostel offers simple dorms and private rooms, with amenities such as a communal kitchen, bar, garden, and fitness center. It has garnered positive feedback for its cleanliness and location. The vibrant atmosphere and chic bar make it an ideal choice for solo travelers looking to socialize.
name: Hopa Home Patagonia Hostel
address: Onelli 125, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: Cerro Catedral is a stunning massif located near Bariloche, Argentina. The area offers mesmerizing views of Lago Nahuel Huapi and the surrounding lakes. The urban planning around the region has its flaws, but the beach still provides pleasant views despite its narrowness. For those interested in skiing, staying near Cerro Catedral is ideal, while those wanting to explore Bariloche should consider accommodations in the city center.
name: Cerro Catedral
address: San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

name: Catedral Mountain School
address: Shopping Las Terrazas, Acceso A Cerro Catedral 1º Piso, Base, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

detail_description: If you're seeking an exhilarating adventure in Bariloche, look no further than Zipline! This thrilling experience takes you soaring through the stunning landscapes of the Piedras Blancas complex on Cerro Otto. With a breathtaking 1500-meter route featuring double lanes, you'll enjoy panoramic views of San Carlos de Bariloche and its picturesque lake. The instructors are not only knowledgeable but also incredibly supportive, ensuring that even those with a bit of anxiety can feel at ease while they fly through the air.
name: Zipline
address: San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

excerpt: Year-round center with a base village offering 1,480 acres of ski & snowboard terrain & 38 lifts.
detail_description: Catedral Alta Patagonia is an all-year-round destination with a variety of entertainment options for ski and snowboard enthusiasts. The base village provides ample access to 1,480 acres of snow-covered terrain via 38 lifts. Visitors can enjoy breathtaking views while skiing on top of the clouds or take a leisurely stroll up the mountain as pedestrians are welcome too.
name: Catedral Alta Patagonia
address: Base cerro Catedral, San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina

excerpt: 11,453-ft. extinct volcano offering challenging ascents to the summit for mountaineers.
detail_description: Tronador, an extinct volcano standing at 11,453 feet, offers challenging ascents to the summit for mountaineers. Located near Bariloche in Argentinean Patagonia, it boasts several peaks and eight glaciers. A trek into this mountain area provides close-up views of several glaciers and the option to stay overnight in mountain huts.
name: Tronador
address: Puerto Varas, Los Lagos, Chile

excerpt: Massive national park established in 1903 with mountains, lakes & forests & outdoors activities.
detail_description: Parque Nacional Nahuel Huapi, established in 1903, is a vast national park in Argentina's Lakes District. Spanning 7500 sq km across Neuquen and Rio Negro provinces, it boasts mountains, lakes, and forests offering various outdoor activities. The centerpiece is the impressive Lago Nahuel Huapi, a glacial lake over 100km long. Hiking enthusiasts can explore challenging multiday treks or easier rambles with well-marked trails.
name: Nahuel Huapi National Park
address: Av. San Martín 24 - San Carlos de Bariloche R8400ALN, Río Negro, Argentina

excerpt: Quirky, verdant park featuring a variety of life-sized dinosaur replicas & an education center.
detail_description: Parque Nahuelito is a charming and educational park located in the small circuit of Bariloche. It features a variety of life-sized dinosaur replicas, making it an exciting destination for families. Visitors can enjoy a guided tour that lasts approximately 35 minutes, during which they can walk among nearly 30 dinosaur specimens. The knowledgeable and friendly guides provide engaging explanations about the dinosaurs, creating an enjoyable experience for both children and adults.
name: Parque Nahuelito
address: Ruta 77 km 24,5, R8400 San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro, Argentina
